{"id":"1807.04556","submitter":"Andreas Cap","authors":"Andreas Cap, A. Rod Gover, and Matthias Hammerl","title":"Parabolic Compactification of Homogeneous Spaces","comments":"38 pages, comments are welcome","journal-ref":"J. Inst. Math. Jussieu 20, no. 4 (2021) 1371-1408","doi":"10.1017/S1474748019000513","report-no":null,"categories":"math.DG math.RT","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  In this article, we study compactifications of homogeneous spaces coming from\nequivariant, open embeddings into a generalized flag manifold $G/P$. The key to\nthis approach is that in each case $G/P$ is the homogeneous model for a\nparabolic geometry; the theory of such geometries provides a large supply of\ngeometric tools and invariant differential operators that can be used for this\nstudy. A classical theorem of J.~Wolf shows that any involutive automorphism of\na semisimple Lie group $G$ with fixed point group $H$ gives rise to a large\nfamily of such compactifications of homogeneous spaces of $H$. Most examples of\n(classical) Riemannian symmetric spaces as well as many non--symmetric examples\narise in this way. A specific feature of the approach is that any\ncompactification of that type comes with the notion of \"curved analog\" to which\nthe tools we develop also apply. The model example of this is a general\nPoincar\\'e--Einstein manifold forming the curved analog of the conformal\ncompactification of hyperbolic space.\n  In the first part of the article, we derive general tools for the analysis of\nsuch compactifications. In the second part, we analyze two families of examples\nin detail, which in particular contain compactifications of the symmetric\nspaces $SL(n,\\Bbb R)/SO(p,n-p)$ and $SO(n,\\Bbb C)/SO(n)$. We describe the\ndecomposition of the compactification into orbits, show how orbit closures can\nbe described as the zero sets of smooth solutions to certain invariant\ndifferential operators and prove a local slice theor