w is separated. This is indicative that a natural forcing mechanism\nkeeps the flow attached against the APG and separated despite the FPG. The\npresent investigation suggests that most of the observations reported in the\nliterature about the LSB and its associated LFO are neither thresholds nor\nindicators for the inception of the instability, but rather are consequences of\nit.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 12 Jul 2018 12:34:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-07-13"}
